{{日本の寺院 |名称 = {{ill|Koyama-ji|ja|甲山寺|12=draft}} |image = Kōyama-ji, Main Hall 001.jpg |imageサイズ = 250 |image説明 = Main Hall |所在地 = {{ill|Kagawa Prefecture|ja|香川県|12=draft}}{{ill|Zentsūji City|ja|善通寺市|12=draft}} 弘田町1765-1 |位置 = {{Coord|34|13|59.5|N|133|45|56.75|E|type:landmark_region:JP-37|display=inline,title}} |山号 = {{ill|Iōzan|ja|医王山|12=draft}} |院号 = {{ill|Taho-in|ja|多宝院|12=draft}} |宗旨 = |宗派 = {{ill|Shingon Shentsū-ji Sect|ja|真言宗善通寺派|12=draft}} |寺格 = |本尊 = {{ill|Yakushi Nyorai|ja|薬師如来|12=draft}} |創建年 = (伝) {{ill|Kōnin|ja|弘仁|12=draft}}12nd year ({{ill|821|ja|821st year|12=draft}}) |開山 = |開基 = (伝) {{ill|Kūkai|ja|空海|12=draft}} ({{ill|Kōbō Daishi|ja|弘法大師|12=draft}}) |中興年 = |中興 = |正式名 = {{ill|Iōzan Taho-in Koyama-ji|ja|医王山 多宝院 甲山寺|12=draft}} |別称 = |札所等 = {{ill|Shikoku 88 Temples|ja|四国八十八箇所|12=draft}} No.74 |文化財 = |公式HP = https://koyamaji.or.jp/ |公式HP名 = [Kagawa] Iōzan Taho-in Koyama-ji |地図2 = {{Switcher | {{Location map+|Japan Kagawa|width=230|caption= |float=center|places= {{Location map~|Japan Kagawa|lat_deg=34|lat_min=13|lat_sec=59.5|lon_deg=133|lon_min=45|lon_sec=56.75|mark=Indian_Swastika.svg|marksize=12|position=left|label={{ill|Koyama-ji|ja|甲山寺|12=draft}}|label_size=100|caption=}} {{Location map~|Japan Kagawa|lat_deg=34|lat_min=21|lat_sec=2.46|lon_deg=134|lon_min=2|lon_sec=48.98|mark=blue pog.svg|position=top|label={{ill|Takamatsu Station (Kagawa)|ja|高松駅|12=draft}}|label_size=95}} {{Location map~|Japan Kagawa|lat_deg=34|lat_min=12|lat_sec=51|lon_deg=134|lon_min=0|lon_sec=56|mark=BSicon FLUGg.svg|marksize=10|position=bottom|label={{ill|Takamatsu Airport|ja|高松空港|12=draft}}|label_size=95}}}} | Position in Kagawa Prefecture | {{maplink2|frame=yes|plain=yes|type=point|zoom=14|frame-align=center|frame-width=230}} | Position in Zentsūji City }} }}
'''Koyama-ji''' (甲山寺, こうやまじ) is a temple of the {{ill|Shingon Shentsū-ji Sect|ja|真言宗善通寺派|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Kagawa Prefecture|ja|香川県|12=draft}}, {{ill|Zentsūji City|ja|善通寺市|12=draft}}. It is also known by its mountain name, {{ill|Iōzan|ja|医王山|12=draft}}, and by its temple name, {{ill|Taho-in|ja|多宝院|12=draft}}. The principal image is {{ill|Yakushi Nyorai|ja|薬師如来|12=draft}}, and it is the 74th temple on the {{ill|Shikoku 88 Temples|ja|四国八十八箇所|12=draft}} pilgrimage. The temple is situated at the foot of {{ill|Koyama (Kagawa)|ja|甲山|12=draft}} (also called Kabutoyama).
* The mantra of the principal image is: "on korokoro sendarimātōgi sowaka" (おん ころころ せんだりまとうぎ そわか). * The temple hymn (ご詠歌) is: "In battles where the Twelve Deities (十二神) are my allies, may my heart be like Koyama" (十二神味方に持てる戦には おのれとこころ甲やまかな). * The Nōkyō seal includes the temple’s principal image, the guardian deity {{ill|Tamonten|ja|多聞天堂毘沙門天|12=draft}}, and a rabbit seal (worth 200 yen).
== Overview == {{File:Kouyamaji20210309 1.jpg|170px|left|thumb|Koyama-ji}} According to legend, during his prime, {{ill|Kūkai|ja|空海|12=draft}} once explored this area—where he had played as a child—and encountered an old man who prophesied that a temple should be built here. Believing the old man to be an incarnation of {{ill|Bishamonten|ja|毘沙門天|12=draft}} who dwelled in a local cave, Kūkai enshrined Bishamonten in that cave. Later, upon receiving an imperial edict from Emperor {{ill|Saga|ja|嵯峨天皇|12=draft}} to rebuild {{ill|Mannō-ike|ja|満濃池|12=draft}}, Kūkai inscribed an image of {{ill|Yakushi Nyorai|ja|薬師如来|12=draft}} and conducted rituals that drew tens of thousands of people, leading to the successful completion tier 1]] == Kōyama-ji == ; [[Shikoku Pilgrimage]] : 73 {{ill|Shusshaka-ji|ja|出釈迦寺|12=draft}} --{{small|(2.2 km)}}-* '''74 Kōyama-ji''' --{{small|(1.6 km)}}-- 75 {{ill|Zentsū-ji|ja|善通寺|12=draft}}
