'''Koyama-ji''' (甲山寺, こうやまじ) is a temple of the {{ill|Shingon Shentsū-ji Sect|ja|真言宗善通寺派|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Kagawa Prefecture|ja|香川県|12=draft}}, {{ill|Zentsūji City|ja|善通寺市|12=draft}}. It is also known by its mountain name, {{ill|Iōzan|ja|医王山|12=draft}}, and by its temple name, {{ill|Taho-in|ja|多宝院|12=draft}}. The principal image is {{ill|Yakushi Nyorai|ja|薬師如来|1=Bhaisajyaguru|lt=Yakushi Nyorai (Me)dicine Buddha|12=draft}}, and it is the 74th temple on the {{ill|Shikoku 88 Temples|ja|四国八十八箇所|12=draft}} pilgrimage. The temple is situated at the foot of {{ill|Koyama (Kagawa)|ja|甲山|12=draft}} (also called Kabutoyama).
* The mantra of the principal image is: "on korokoro sendarimātōgi sowaka" (おん ころころ せんだりまとうぎ そわか). * The temple hymn (ご詠歌) is: "In battles where the Twelve Deities (十二神) are my allies, may my heart be like Koyama" (十二神味方に持てる戦には おのれとこころ甲やまかな). * The Nōkyō seal includes the temple’s principal image, the guardian deity {{ill|Tamonten|ja|多聞天堂毘沙門天|12=draft}}, and a rabbit seal (worth 200 yen).
