'''Koyama-ji''' (甲山寺, こうやまじ) is a temple of the {{ill|Shingon Shentsū-ji Sect|ja|真言宗善通寺派|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shingon Shentsū-ji Sect|qq=}} located in {{ill|Kagawa Prefecture|ja|香川県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kagawa Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Zentsūji City|ja|善通寺市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zentsūji City|qq=}}. It is also known by its mountain name, {{ill|Iōzan|ja|医王山|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iōzan|qq=}}, and by its temple name, {{ill|Taho-in|ja|多宝院|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taho-in|qq=}}. The principal image is {{ill|Yakushi Nyorai|ja|薬師如来|1=Bhaisajyaguru|lt=Yakushi Nyorai Medicine Buddha|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yakushi Nyorai|13=User:Immanuelle/Bhaisajyaguru|qq=}}, and it is the 74th temple on the {{ill|Shikoku 88 Temples|ja|四国八十八箇所|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikoku 88 Temples|qq=}} pilgrimage. The temple is situated at the foot of {{ill|Koyama (Kagawa)|ja|甲山|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koyama (Kagawa)|qq=}} (also called Kabutoyama).

* The mantra of the principal image is: "on korokoro sendarimātōgi sowaka" (おん ころころ せんだりまとうぎ そわか).
* The temple hymn (ご詠歌) is: "In battles where the Twelve Deities (十二神) are my allies, may my heart be like Koyama" (十二神味方に持てる戦には　おのれとこころ甲やまかな).
* The Nōkyō seal includes the temple’s principal image, the guardian deity {{ill|Tamonten|ja|多聞天堂毘沙門天|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamonten|qq=}}, and a rabbit seal (worth 200 yen).

== Overview ==
{{File:Kouyamaji20210309 1.jpg|170px|left|thumb|Koyama-ji}}
According to legend, during his prime, {{ill|Kūkai|ja|空海|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kūkai|qq=}} once explored this area—where he had played as a child—and encountered an old man who prophesied that a temple should be built here. Believing the old man to be an incarnation of {{ill|Bishamonten|ja|毘沙門天|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bishamonten|qq=}} who dwelled in a local cave, Kūkai enshrined Bishamonten in that cave.
Later, upon receiving an imperial edict from Emperor {{ill|Saga|ja|嵯峨天皇|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saga|qq=}} to rebuild {{ill|Mannō-ike|ja|満濃池|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mannō-ike|qq=}}, Kūkai inscribed an image of {{ill|Yakushi Nyorai|ja|薬師如来|1=Bhaisajyaguru|lt=Yakushi Nyorai Medicine Buddha|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yakushi Nyorai|13=User:Immanuelle/Bhaisajyaguru|qq=}} and conducted rituals that drew tens of thousands of people, leading to the successful Completion tier 1]]
