{{日本の寺院 |名称 = {{ill|Koyama-ji|ja|甲山寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koyama-ji|qq=}} |image = Kōyama-ji, Main Hall 001.jpg |imageサイズ = 250 |image説明 = Main Hall |所在地 = [[:en:Kagawa Prefecture|Kagawa Prefecture]][[:en:Zentsūji, Kagawa|Zentsūji City]] 弘田町1765-1 |位置 = {{Coord|34|13|59.5|N|133|45|56.75|E|type:landmark_region:JP-37|display=inline,title}} |山号 = [[:en:Iozen|Iōzan]] |院号 = {{ill|Taho-in|ja|多宝院|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taho-in|qq=}} |宗旨 = |宗派 = {{ill|Shingon Shentsū-ji Sect|ja|真言宗善通寺派|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shingon Shentsū-ji Sect|qq=}} |寺格 = |本尊 = [[:en:Bhaisajyaguru|Yakushi Nyorai Medicine Buddha]] |創建年 = (伝) [[:en:Kōnin (era)|Kōnin]]12nd year ([[:en:821|821]]) |開山 = |開基 = (伝) [[:en:Kūkai|Kūkai]] ({{ill|Kōbō Daishi|ja|弘法大師|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōbō Daishi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 空海}}) |中興年 = |中興 = |正式名 = {{ill|Iōzan Taho-in Koyama-ji|ja|医王山 多宝院 甲山寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iōzan Taho-in Koyama-ji|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} |別称 = |札所等 = [[:en:Shikoku Pilgrimage|Shikoku 88 Temples]] No.74 |文化財 = |公式HP = https://koyamaji.or.jp/ |公式HP名 = [Kagawa] Iōzan Taho-in Koyama-ji |地図2 = {{Switcher | {{Location map+|Japan Kagawa|width=230|caption= |float=center|places= {{Location map~|Japan Kagawa|lat_deg=34|lat_min=13|lat_sec=59.5|lon_deg=133|lon_min=45|lon_sec=56.75|mark=Indian_Swastika.svg|marksize=12|position=left|label={{ill|Koyama-ji|ja|甲山寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koyama-ji|qq=}}|label_size=100|caption=}} {{Location map~|Japan Kagawa|lat_deg=34|lat_min=21|lat_sec=2.46|lon_deg=134|lon_min=2|lon_sec=48.98|mark=blue pog.svg|position=top|label=[[:en:Takamatsu Station|Takamatsu Station (Kagawa)]]|label_size=95}} {{Location map~|Japan Kagawa|lat_deg=34|lat_min=12|lat_sec=51|lon_deg=134|lon_min=0|lon_sec=56|mark=BSicon FLUGg.svg|marksize=10|position=bottom|label=[[:en:Takamatsu Airport|Takamatsu Airport]]|label_size=95}}}} | Position in Kagawa Prefecture | {{maplink2|frame=yes|plain=yes|type=point|zoom=14|frame-align=center|frame-width=230}} | Position in Zentsūji City }} }}
'''Koyama-ji''' (甲山寺, こうやまじ) is a temple of the {{ill|Shingon Shentsū-ji Sect|ja|真言宗善通寺派|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shingon Shentsū-ji Sect|qq=}} located in [[:en:Kagawa Prefecture|Kagawa Prefecture]], [[:en:Zentsūji, Kagawa|Zentsūji City]]. It is also known by its mountain name, [[:en:Iozen|Iōzan]], and by its temple name, {{ill|Taho-in|ja|多宝院|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taho-in|qq=}}. The principal image is [[:en:Bhaisajyaguru|Yakushi Nyorai Medicine Buddha]], and it is the 74th temple on the [[:en:Shikoku Pilgrimage|Shikoku 88 Temples]] pilgrimage. The temple is situated at the foot of [[:en:Mount Kabuto|Koyama (Kagawa)]] (also called Kabutoyama).
* The mantra of the principal image is: "on korokoro sendarimātōgi sowaka" (おん ころころ せんだりまとうぎ そわか). * The temple hymn (ご詠歌) is: "In battles where the Twelve Deities (十二神) are my allies, may my heart be like Koyama" (十二神味方に持てる戦には おのれとこころ甲やまかな). * The Nōkyō seal includes the temple’s principal image, the guardian deity {{ill|Tamonten|ja|多聞天堂毘沙門天|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamonten|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, and a rabbit seal (worth 200 yen).
== Overview == {{File:Kouyamaji20210309 1.jpg|170px|left|thumb|Koyama-ji}} According to legend, during his prime, [[:en:Kūkai|Kūkai]] once explored this area—where he had played as a child—and encountered an old man who prophesied that a temple should be built here. Believing the old man to be an incarnation of [[:en:Vaiśravaṇa|Bishamonten]] who dwelled in a local cave, Kūkai enshrined Bishamonten in that cave. Later, upon receiving an imperial edict from Emperor [[:en:Emperor Saga|Saga]] to rebuild [[:en:Manno Lake|Mannō-ike]], Kūkai inscribed an image of [[:en:Bhaisajyaguru|Yakushi Nyorai Medicine Buddha]] and conducted rituals that drew tens of thousands of people, leading to the successful Completion tier 1]] == Kōyama-ji == ; [[:en:Shikoku Pilgrimage|Shikoku Pilgrimage]] : 73 {{ill|Shusshaka-ji|ja|出釈迦寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shusshaka-ji|qq=}} --{{small|(2.2 km)}}-* '''74 Kōyama-ji''' --{{small|(1.6 km)}}-- 75 [[:en:Zentsū-ji|Zentsū-ji]]
