'''Koyama-ji''' (甲山寺, こうやまじ) is a temple of the {{ill|Shingon Shentsū-ji Sect|ja|真言宗善通寺派|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shingon Shentsū-ji Sect|qq=}} located in [[:en:Kagawa Prefecture|Kagawa Prefecture]], [[:en:Zentsūji, Kagawa|Zentsūji City]]. It is also known by its mountain name, [[:en:Iozen|Iōzan]], and by its temple name, {{ill|Taho-in|ja|多宝院|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taho-in|qq=}}. The principal image is [[:en:Bhaisajyaguru|Yakushi Nyorai Medicine Buddha]], and it is the 74th temple on the [[:en:Shikoku Pilgrimage|Shikoku 88 Temples]] pilgrimage. The temple is situated at the foot of [[:en:Mount Kabuto|Koyama (Kagawa)]] (also called Kabutoyama).
* The mantra of the principal image is: "on korokoro sendarimātōgi sowaka" (おん ころころ せんだりまとうぎ そわか). * The temple hymn (ご詠歌) is: "In battles where the Twelve Deities (十二神) are my allies, may my heart be like Koyama" (十二神味方に持てる戦には おのれとこころ甲やまかな). * The Nōkyō seal includes the temple’s principal image, the guardian deity {{ill|Tamonten|ja|多聞天堂毘沙門天|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamonten|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, and a rabbit seal (worth 200 yen).
